{
  "id": "ramp-travel-api-top-spenders",
  "kind": "problem",
  "title": "Travel API Top Spenders",
  "difficulty": "medium",
  "concepts": [
    "multi-step API workflow",
    "aggregation",
    "sorting"
  ],
  "timeboxMinutes": 30,
  "prompt": "Finance wants the top employees by total trip spend. There is no single endpoint that returns the answer.\n\nWrite `top_spenders(base_url, token, n=5)`. First page through `GET /v1/employees`. Then, for each employee, call `GET /v1/employees/{employee_id}/trips`. Sum `total_cost_cents` per employee and return the top `n` spenders.\n\nReturn contract:\n\n- Return a list of 2-item pairs: `[(employee_id, total_cents), ...]`. Returning inner lists also serializes correctly in this app, but tuples are idiomatic Python.\n- Sort by `total_cents` descending.\n- Skip employees with zero trip spend.\n- Respect the `n` argument.\n- If nobody has spend, return `[]`.\n\nEndpoint details:\n\n- `GET {base_url}/v1/employees` is paginated and requires auth.\n- `GET {base_url}/v1/employees/{employee_id}/trips` requires auth and returns `{\"data\": [trip_dict, ...]}`.\n- Trip dicts include `total_cost_cents`.\n\nThe test harness passes `token` into your function. Do not define or hardcode it; use the `token` parameter when building the `Authorization` header.\n\nInvariants and corner cases:\n\n- Fetch every employee page before ranking.\n- Include all trips for each employee.\n- Sort once after computing totals; do not return the first `n` positive spenders you happen to see.\n- Do not include zero-spend employees.\n\nShared fake API note: this uses the in-process `requests` mock described in the Ramp Travel module guide; there is no real network.\n\nValidation focus: multi-step API workflow, employee pagination, totals, descending sort, uniqueness, and `n`.",
  "signature": {
    "name": "topSpenders",
    "inputs": [
      {
        "name": "base_url",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "token",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "n",
        "type": {
          "type": "number"
        }
      }
    ],
    "output": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "any"
      }
    }
  },
